# Deny-by-default: ignore everything, then allow only the files we
# explicitly track. Adding a new file requires updating the allowlist —
# surfaces the decision instead of letting it slip in via `git add .`.
#
# README.private.md (plaintext) is intentionally NOT allowlisted —
# only the encrypted README.private.md.gpg may be committed.

*

!.gitignore
!README.md
!README.private.md.gpg
!init-from-bitwarden.sh
